1
00:00:00,120 --> 00:00:01,360
Five million?

2
00:00:02,460 --> 00:00:05,830
[Episode 5: To protect you
from the world's malice]

3
00:00:03,220 --> 00:00:05,220
That amount doesn't make any sense.

4
00:00:06,940 --> 00:00:08,500
May I ask you something?

5
00:00:08,970 --> 00:00:11,800
Mr. He, what do you do?

6
00:00:13,470 --> 00:00:14,530
I run a guesthouse.

7
00:00:16,260 --> 00:00:18,360
With a guesthouse income like that...

8
00:00:18,360 --> 00:00:19,510
Well, it's not really your fault.

9
00:00:19,510 --> 00:00:20,950
You may not know

10
00:00:20,980 --> 00:00:21,880
how

11
00:00:22,620 --> 00:00:23,670
the market works.

12
00:00:23,700 --> 00:00:25,430
Actually, the five million...

13
00:00:26,140 --> 00:00:26,670
It's like this.

14
00:00:26,670 --> 00:00:27,340
Our company

15
00:00:27,340 --> 00:00:29,340
signed a contract with the artists.

16
00:00:29,440 --> 00:00:31,610
There are also upstream
and downstream agreements,

17
00:00:31,610 --> 00:00:33,410
and the cost of the printed materials
that were scrapped this time—

18
00:00:33,410 --> 00:00:35,410
Adding it all up, this five million.

19
00:00:35,880 --> 00:00:37,200
Seriously.

20
00:00:37,550 --> 00:00:39,720
That's already the lowest

21
00:00:40,290 --> 00:00:42,020
I could possibly get it down to.

22
00:00:44,790 --> 00:00:45,720
How about this?

23
00:00:46,160 --> 00:00:48,190
Show me the contracts one by one.

24
00:00:48,690 --> 00:00:50,160
And we'll check them one by one

25
00:00:50,160 --> 00:00:52,560
to see if there really
is such a high amount.

26
00:00:53,530 --> 00:00:54,900
I might not have them with me right now.

27
00:00:54,900 --> 00:00:55,890
But I think

28
00:00:56,030 --> 00:00:57,370
something is more important
for you to check out.

29
00:00:57,370 --> 00:00:58,030
Well...

30
00:01:01,930 --> 00:01:04,530
Please take a look at this document.

31
00:01:04,900 --> 00:01:06,170
Xiangyong signed it.

32
00:01:06,210 --> 00:01:08,390
[Voluntary Resignation Waiver]

33
00:01:07,010 --> 00:01:08,410
I also checked it with him

34
00:01:09,050 --> 00:01:10,120
many times.

35
00:01:13,789 --> 00:01:14,920
It's such a high amount.

36
00:01:14,920 --> 00:01:17,160
And you expect Xiangyong
to take all of it?

37
00:01:17,160 --> 00:01:17,930
Boss.

38
00:01:17,990 --> 00:01:18,920
-Are you…
-Sorry.

39
00:01:18,920 --> 00:01:19,980
I'm the president.

40
00:01:23,190 --> 00:01:24,160
President.

41
00:01:25,500 --> 00:01:27,100
Are you using him as a scapegoat

42
00:01:27,100 --> 00:01:28,640
just because he's young?

43
00:01:35,170 --> 00:01:36,110
Mr. He,

44
00:01:36,810 --> 00:01:38,870
hearing you say that honestly hurts.

45
00:01:40,810 --> 00:01:43,070
To be honest, when I started my busniess,

46
00:01:43,110 --> 00:01:44,880
what I wanted the most

47
00:01:44,880 --> 00:01:46,450
was to be fair and open.

48
00:01:47,090 --> 00:01:48,750
Although our company is not big,

49
00:01:48,750 --> 00:01:51,150
we run
a very principled publishing house.

50
00:01:53,100 --> 00:01:53,970
It's okay.

51
00:01:54,090 --> 00:01:54,660
Mr. He.

52
00:01:55,160 --> 00:01:56,890
It's okay if you don't trust me.

53
00:01:56,900 --> 00:01:57,960
I'll ask Xiangyong's former colleagues

54
00:01:57,960 --> 00:01:59,770
to explain to you.

55
00:01:59,800 --> 00:02:00,210
OK?

56
00:02:01,770 --> 00:02:03,970
This is He Xiangyong's father.

57
00:02:04,300 --> 00:02:06,140
He thinks we misunderstood him.

58
00:02:07,010 --> 00:02:09,169
He really messed things up.

59
00:02:09,169 --> 00:02:11,380
The whole company
was a mess because of him.

60
00:02:11,380 --> 00:02:11,840
Yes.

61
00:02:11,840 --> 00:02:13,880
I've been cleaning up his mess.

62
00:02:13,880 --> 00:02:14,590
Mr. He,

63
00:02:14,780 --> 00:02:17,150
ever since he was an intern,

64
00:02:17,150 --> 00:02:19,079
he's been messing up

65
00:02:19,079 --> 00:02:20,190
nonstop.

66
00:02:20,190 --> 00:02:22,190
We're always cleaning up after him.

67
00:02:22,300 --> 00:02:23,440
That's enough.

68
00:02:23,890 --> 00:02:24,990
What's going on?

69
00:02:25,290 --> 00:02:28,020
His father is here,
and you're talking like that.

70
00:02:32,660 --> 00:02:34,900
If it really is Xiangyong's fault,

71
00:02:38,740 --> 00:02:39,840
then I thank you

72
00:02:40,610 --> 00:02:42,740
for taking care of him all these years.

73
00:02:43,340 --> 00:02:45,270
If you all have a clear conscience,

74
00:02:46,540 --> 00:02:48,480
then I also wish your company
a prosperous business

75
00:02:48,480 --> 00:02:49,940
and flourishing success.

76
00:02:50,180 --> 00:02:51,350
May you don't choke on your food.

77
00:02:51,350 --> 00:02:52,079
May you never trip while walking.

78
00:02:52,079 --> 00:02:52,820
Hope you never run

79
00:02:52,820 --> 00:02:54,350
into another He Xiangyong!

80
00:02:58,400 --> 00:02:59,060
Mr. He,

81
00:02:59,090 --> 00:03:00,610
that was really well said.

82
00:03:00,630 --> 00:03:01,890
I am really moved, really.

83
00:03:01,890 --> 00:03:03,190
For people like us
who come out to do business,

84
00:03:03,190 --> 00:03:04,330
the last thing we want

85
00:03:04,330 --> 00:03:06,330
is an employee like Xiangyong.

86
00:03:08,030 --> 00:03:08,770
By the way,

87
00:03:09,270 --> 00:03:10,500
Xiangyong's friend called

88
00:03:10,500 --> 00:03:12,000
and said they would handle this matter.

89
00:03:12,000 --> 00:03:12,940
But actually, until now,

90
00:03:12,940 --> 00:03:14,740
we still haven't heard any news.

91
00:03:15,540 --> 00:03:16,610
I want to remind you, Mr. He,

92
00:03:16,610 --> 00:03:17,579
if that's the case,

93
00:03:17,579 --> 00:03:18,210
we might have to

94
00:03:18,210 --> 00:03:21,050
take legal action later on.

95
00:03:26,850 --> 00:03:29,150
Don't use the law to threaten me.

96
00:03:32,320 --> 00:03:35,050
He Xiangyong said
he would take responsibility.

97
00:03:36,060 --> 00:03:38,390
So we will take responsibility to the end.

98
00:03:39,760 --> 00:03:40,930
Then sorry to trouble you again.

99
00:03:40,930 --> 00:03:42,400
See Mr. He out.

100
00:04:32,950 --> 00:04:36,190
[Wishing Upon the Shooting Stars]

101
00:04:36,650 --> 00:04:38,659
What kind of heartless company is this?

102
00:04:38,659 --> 00:04:40,990
This is practically workplace bullying.

103
00:04:41,890 --> 00:04:43,659
That idiot kid of mine

104
00:04:44,260 --> 00:04:45,800
came back to the island

105
00:04:46,820 --> 00:04:48,690
and refused to tell me anything.

106
00:04:49,800 --> 00:04:51,510
Of course, he takes after you.

107
00:04:52,100 --> 00:04:53,630
Xiangyong is just like you.

108
00:04:54,440 --> 00:04:57,100
He'd never let you see
how much he's struggling.

109
00:04:57,180 --> 00:04:57,909
And you won't let him know

110
00:04:57,909 --> 00:04:59,210
that something's wrong with your kidneys.

111
00:04:59,210 --> 00:05:00,450
You're the one with an enlarged prostate.

112
00:05:00,450 --> 00:05:01,150
Who has a problem?

113
00:05:01,150 --> 00:05:02,380
Keep it down.

114
00:05:03,170 --> 00:05:04,330
It's just health stuff, nothing serious.

115
00:05:04,330 --> 00:05:06,160
There's nothing to talk about.

116
00:05:07,150 --> 00:05:08,720
Yeah, right.

117
00:05:09,220 --> 00:05:10,420
Every time Xiangyong comes back,

118
00:05:10,420 --> 00:05:12,020
you just sit there drinking.

119
00:05:12,140 --> 00:05:12,770
And then?

120
00:05:12,820 --> 00:05:14,750
You prepare the freshest seafood.

121
00:05:15,030 --> 00:05:16,090
Anyone can see

122
00:05:16,120 --> 00:05:17,830
that you're happy when Xiangyong is back.

123
00:05:17,830 --> 00:05:19,430
You call that a minor matter?

124
00:05:23,640 --> 00:05:24,640
So what now?

125
00:05:25,460 --> 00:05:27,260
The only way is to sell the house?

126
00:05:30,880 --> 00:05:32,600
I went to the bank for a loan.

127
00:05:33,900 --> 00:05:36,230
But the house is too old
and not worth much.

128
00:05:37,620 --> 00:05:38,780
I'm old, too.

129
00:05:39,250 --> 00:05:40,780
And I don't want a day to come

130
00:05:41,620 --> 00:05:42,490
after I'm gone

131
00:05:42,490 --> 00:05:44,890
where Xiangyong
still has to carry my debt.

132
00:05:47,290 --> 00:05:48,220
Fortunately...

133
00:05:48,330 --> 00:05:49,290
fortunately, that David guy

134
00:05:49,290 --> 00:05:51,330
offered just that little bit more.

135
00:05:52,659 --> 00:05:53,520
Sell the house?

136
00:05:54,020 --> 00:05:56,280
Of course, I'll sell it, sell it quickly.

137
00:05:58,090 --> 00:06:00,430
You mean that influencer, David?

138
00:06:02,940 --> 00:06:04,020
He is very sincere.

139
00:06:04,480 --> 00:06:06,010
He's not from our island.

140
00:06:06,010 --> 00:06:07,480
The moment he knows I decided
to sell the house,

141
00:06:07,480 --> 00:06:09,580
he said
he'd take a boat to see it.

142
00:06:09,580 --> 00:06:11,220
I'm grateful to him, too.

143
00:06:23,660 --> 00:06:25,190
Why are you cutting so much?

144
00:06:26,190 --> 00:06:27,400
Don't sneak a bite.

145
00:06:27,830 --> 00:06:29,560
That's for other people to eat.

146
00:06:35,770 --> 00:06:37,040
Look, they're here.

147
00:06:37,370 --> 00:06:38,570
Get it ready quickly.

148
00:06:38,780 --> 00:06:40,140
Stop cutting already.

149
00:06:41,030 --> 00:06:42,630
Snake-style throw.

150
00:06:44,950 --> 00:06:46,280
Mr. He.

151
00:06:47,890 --> 00:06:49,450
Careful.

152
00:06:49,450 --> 00:06:51,260
Be careful.

153
00:06:53,000 --> 00:06:54,210
Nice catch.

154
00:06:55,130 --> 00:06:57,310
This is a gift for our meeting.

155
00:06:57,730 --> 00:07:00,300
This is the crystal I recently released.

156
00:07:00,330 --> 00:07:01,130
A crystal—

157
00:07:01,130 --> 00:07:02,350
It looks pretty good, right?

158
00:07:02,350 --> 00:07:03,610
Good.

159
00:07:03,630 --> 00:07:04,870
This is my good friend,

160
00:07:04,870 --> 00:07:05,680
Mr. Hua.

161
00:07:05,790 --> 00:07:07,900
Hello, Mr. Hua.

162
00:07:09,140 --> 00:07:10,380
Have a seat here.

163
00:07:10,380 --> 00:07:11,780
It's so hot.

164
00:07:11,800 --> 00:07:13,900
This weather is a characteristic
of our Xingpu Island.

165
00:07:13,900 --> 00:07:16,030
It's like a fairy tale world, you know?

166
00:07:16,280 --> 00:07:17,280
Actually, it's quite comfortable.

167
00:07:17,280 --> 00:07:18,680
What do you want to drink?

168
00:07:18,820 --> 00:07:19,880
Bull energy drink.

169
00:07:20,920 --> 00:07:22,790
Xiaoyou, get a can of Bull.

170
00:07:23,760 --> 00:07:24,860
Take a photo.

171
00:07:24,860 --> 00:07:26,120
These are all old houses.

172
00:07:26,120 --> 00:07:27,360
You don't see them much anymore.

173
00:07:27,360 --> 00:07:29,130
They're my employees.

174
00:07:29,560 --> 00:07:31,060
Take a photo of
that dilapidated building, too.

175
00:07:31,060 --> 00:07:32,770
See what places can be renovated.

176
00:07:32,770 --> 00:07:34,200
Film it.

177
00:07:35,170 --> 00:07:36,750
Just film whatever.

178
00:07:45,640 --> 00:07:46,710
What are you doing?

179
00:07:52,650 --> 00:07:54,650
This is my old trade.

180
00:07:54,720 --> 00:07:56,420
I thought if I can't even do this well,

181
00:07:56,420 --> 00:07:59,350
how would I have money
to buy the guesthouse from you?

182
00:07:59,860 --> 00:08:00,760
You're being too polite.

183
00:08:00,760 --> 00:08:01,860
David,

184
00:08:03,360 --> 00:08:04,750
I've heard of your great name
for a long time.

185
00:08:04,750 --> 00:08:05,740
I've watched your videos.

186
00:08:05,740 --> 00:08:07,300
I've subscribed to your channel.

187
00:08:07,300 --> 00:08:08,570
His video content is super rich.

188
00:08:08,570 --> 00:08:10,700
And the view counts are all super high.

189
00:08:11,340 --> 00:08:13,770
Vlogs, diving, food unboxing...

190
00:08:13,770 --> 00:08:15,570
It's all pretty cheap-looking.

191
00:08:19,810 --> 00:08:20,680
Cheerful and sunny

192
00:08:20,680 --> 00:08:22,410
I mean, uh… cheerful and sunny!

193
00:08:24,480 --> 00:08:26,880
But I heard that lately,

194
00:08:26,910 --> 00:08:29,310
you can actually buy views
and traffic now.

195
00:08:30,560 --> 00:08:31,720
I don't really understand it.

196
00:08:31,720 --> 00:08:33,159
So, I thought I'd ask for advice.

197
00:08:33,159 --> 00:08:34,820
Because I don't run a channel.

198
00:08:35,140 --> 00:08:37,210
I have heard about that myself.

199
00:08:37,299 --> 00:08:38,130
But I don't know

200
00:08:38,130 --> 00:08:39,830
how to buy those things.

201
00:08:39,830 --> 00:08:41,960
I've always just done things on my own.

202
00:08:41,970 --> 00:08:43,600
I don't know how to buy them.

203
00:08:43,600 --> 00:08:44,100
Correct.

204
00:08:44,100 --> 00:08:45,770
Just like now I want
to buy the guesthouse,

205
00:08:45,770 --> 00:08:48,610
I'd like to ask Mr. He Xiang for advice

206
00:08:48,610 --> 00:08:50,110
on how to run a guesthouse.

207
00:08:51,680 --> 00:08:53,480
Mr. He, so,

208
00:08:54,350 --> 00:08:56,210
will you be handling the notary work,

209
00:08:56,210 --> 00:08:57,670
or should I take care of it?

210
00:08:58,180 --> 00:09:00,800
You've got more experience
with this kind of thing.

211
00:09:00,800 --> 00:09:01,820
I'll leave it all to you.

212
00:09:01,820 --> 00:09:03,520
Sure.

213
00:09:03,520 --> 00:09:04,650
Then I'll handle it.

214
00:09:05,360 --> 00:09:06,190
Well, excuse me.

215
00:09:06,190 --> 00:09:07,360
I want to ask,

216
00:09:07,360 --> 00:09:09,690
since your channel is so successful,

217
00:09:09,690 --> 00:09:11,800
why get into real estate?

218
00:09:12,610 --> 00:09:13,430
Investing, well,

219
00:09:13,430 --> 00:09:14,870
there are always risks.

220
00:09:14,870 --> 00:09:17,540
And not everything
can be turned into a side gig.

221
00:09:17,540 --> 00:09:19,190
My dad tells me most often:

222
00:09:19,300 --> 00:09:21,070
if a person is too greedy,

223
00:09:21,070 --> 00:09:23,010
it usually doesn't end well.

224
00:09:25,440 --> 00:09:26,280
That's not it for me.

225
00:09:26,280 --> 00:09:28,180
Because for my other jobs,

226
00:09:28,180 --> 00:09:30,210
I make money pretty effortlessly.

227
00:09:30,720 --> 00:09:32,020
So I thought,

228
00:09:32,020 --> 00:09:33,680
for running a guesthouse,
I could get hands-on with it

229
00:09:33,680 --> 00:09:36,030
and really experience local life
for myself.

230
00:09:36,030 --> 00:09:37,170
Where's my Bull?

231
00:09:38,990 --> 00:09:39,660
Where's the Bull?

232
00:09:39,660 --> 00:09:41,530
Haowei, that Bull?

233
00:09:41,530 --> 00:09:42,530
We're out of Bull.

234
00:09:43,060 --> 00:09:44,130
Is that yogurt drink okay?

235
00:09:44,130 --> 00:09:45,390
Forget it, never mind.

236
00:09:46,280 --> 00:09:46,850
Mr. He,

237
00:09:47,470 --> 00:09:48,570
I'm thinking

238
00:09:48,600 --> 00:09:51,730
of tearing the whole place down.

239
00:09:55,650 --> 00:09:58,150
I feel it's a bit too old.

240
00:09:58,180 --> 00:09:59,910
And it's not that safe, either.

241
00:10:00,280 --> 00:10:02,150
So I thought I could
turn it into something like

242
00:10:02,150 --> 00:10:03,250
Greek style,

243
00:10:03,250 --> 00:10:04,150
Turkish style,

244
00:10:04,150 --> 00:10:05,780
Spanish style, anything is fine.

245
00:10:05,780 --> 00:10:06,780
Or is there some—

246
00:10:07,490 --> 00:10:08,720
Or is there some style you want?

247
00:10:08,720 --> 00:10:09,790
You can tell me...

248
00:10:09,790 --> 00:10:10,640
David,

249
00:10:10,860 --> 00:10:12,790
you really don't understand.

250
00:10:13,760 --> 00:10:15,690
Do you know this is a historic site?

251
00:10:15,860 --> 00:10:17,790
Do you know how much history it has?

252
00:10:17,860 --> 00:10:19,360
Do you know how many people come here

253
00:10:19,360 --> 00:10:20,700
because it looks like this?

254
00:10:20,700 --> 00:10:22,770
You really don't get it, do you?

255
00:10:22,870 --> 00:10:24,740
I don't think you should
invest in real estate.

256
00:10:24,740 --> 00:10:26,440
I think you should go back
to filming your cheap-looking Vlogs.

257
00:10:26,440 --> 00:10:27,670
Zhong Xiaoyou!

258
00:10:30,240 --> 00:10:31,840
Don't be rude to my guest.

259
00:10:33,300 --> 00:10:35,230
We'll talk about this later, okay?

260
00:10:35,710 --> 00:10:37,310
Do you really have to sell it?

261
00:10:39,250 --> 00:10:40,850
Is there really no other way?

262
00:10:52,800 --> 00:10:55,300
It's my house. I get to decide.

263
00:10:58,900 --> 00:10:59,970
I'm sorry.

264
00:11:01,540 --> 00:11:02,570
Mr. Hua, it's fine.

265
00:11:02,570 --> 00:11:04,900
You all should discuss it clearly first.

266
00:11:04,920 --> 00:11:06,790
No, it's not like that.

267
00:11:06,880 --> 00:11:07,410
I'm selling it.

268
00:11:07,410 --> 00:11:07,880
I'm definitely selling it.

269
00:11:07,880 --> 00:11:08,580
Okay, okay.

270
00:11:08,580 --> 00:11:09,310
Let me tell you,

271
00:11:09,310 --> 00:11:11,570
I have a rooftop on the second floor, too.

272
00:11:11,620 --> 00:11:12,280
You get a full ocean view there.

273
00:11:12,280 --> 00:11:12,980
I'll take you to see it.

274
00:11:12,980 --> 00:11:13,450
Okay.

275
00:11:13,450 --> 00:11:14,450
Let's go.

276
00:11:14,450 --> 00:11:15,520
This way, please.

277
00:11:17,050 --> 00:11:18,120
You're Zhong Xiaoyou,

278
00:11:18,120 --> 00:11:18,670
right?

279
00:11:20,460 --> 00:11:22,590
Are you afraid of becoming unemployed?

280
00:11:22,590 --> 00:11:23,930
You don't have to worry.

281
00:11:24,560 --> 00:11:26,630
After I buy this guesthouse,

282
00:11:26,630 --> 00:11:28,610
all of you can come and help me.

283
00:11:29,630 --> 00:11:30,770
No, it's not like that.

284
00:11:30,770 --> 00:11:32,040
This way, please.

285
00:11:32,040 --> 00:11:33,270
Let's go.

286
00:11:33,570 --> 00:11:34,340
Turn left ahead.

287
00:11:34,340 --> 00:11:35,070
Take a look.

288
00:11:35,910 --> 00:11:37,110
After turning right,

289
00:11:37,110 --> 00:11:39,840
the view connects
straight out to the ocean.

290
00:11:41,710 --> 00:11:42,710
Haowei, Xiaoyou.

291
00:11:43,640 --> 00:11:45,570
Show them around the place.

292
00:11:46,480 --> 00:11:47,100
Okay.

293
00:11:48,190 --> 00:11:49,220
What's with you?

294
00:11:49,390 --> 00:11:50,790
You're acting very unusually today.

295
00:11:50,790 --> 00:11:51,470
Xiaoyou.

296
00:11:56,790 --> 00:11:57,560
Well,

297
00:11:58,270 --> 00:11:59,130
let's go to the counter.

298
00:11:59,130 --> 00:12:00,260
Come, follow me.

299
00:12:01,370 --> 00:12:02,370
This way.

300
00:12:03,200 --> 00:12:05,100
This is our counter.

301
00:12:32,900 --> 00:12:34,180
No way.

302
00:12:34,200 --> 00:12:36,060
He actually bought it from Yilan.

303
00:12:39,300 --> 00:12:42,110
Hama-chan was actually right.

304
00:12:43,150 --> 00:12:44,810
He said if you have doubts,

305
00:12:44,810 --> 00:12:46,440
just go check his IG stories.

306
00:13:10,320 --> 00:13:11,990
Seeing you eat so happily...

307
00:13:12,010 --> 00:13:13,870
You two have made up, haven't you?

308
00:13:15,040 --> 00:13:16,650
Your son's pretty open-minded, you know.

309
00:13:16,650 --> 00:13:18,850
Friends don't hold grudges overnight.

310
00:13:19,550 --> 00:13:21,080
Are you still just friends?

311
00:13:21,610 --> 00:13:23,510
Don't you like Hama-chan?

312
00:13:23,780 --> 00:13:24,620
I don't like him.

313
00:13:24,620 --> 00:13:25,820
Don't talk nonsense.

314
00:13:27,850 --> 00:13:29,250
Liking someone

315
00:13:29,250 --> 00:13:31,060
is not an embarrassing thing.

316
00:13:31,060 --> 00:13:31,990
I'm telling you—

317
00:13:32,060 --> 00:13:35,130
If you like someone,
just say it out loud.

318
00:13:35,130 --> 00:13:36,390
I don't like him.

319
00:13:38,430 --> 00:13:39,760
It's Uncle Hua's birthday tomorrow.

320
00:13:39,760 --> 00:13:41,230
You have to ask Hama-chan to come.

321
00:13:41,230 --> 00:13:42,140
I'll see.

322
00:13:43,970 --> 00:13:45,150
Li Wanzhe, get on.

323
00:13:45,200 --> 00:13:47,070
-Do you want to eat something first?
-Hurry up.

324
00:13:47,070 --> 00:13:48,510
What?

325
00:13:48,510 --> 00:13:49,710
You're in such a rush.

326
00:13:50,560 --> 00:13:52,090
Mom, I'm going out for a bit.

327
00:13:53,310 --> 00:13:54,910
Are you taking me out to play?

328
00:13:56,150 --> 00:13:57,950
Why are you riding so fast today?

329
00:14:01,350 --> 00:14:01,990
Follow me.

330
00:14:01,990 --> 00:14:03,890
Wait, I haven't taken off my helmet yet.

331
00:14:03,890 --> 00:14:04,560
Hurry up.

332
00:14:04,560 --> 00:14:06,560
What are you doing, being so rushed?

333
00:14:07,730 --> 00:14:09,190
Why are you in such a hurry?

334
00:14:10,230 --> 00:14:11,300
Are you running an errand for a guest?

335
00:14:11,300 --> 00:14:12,830
Do you have your ID with you?

336
00:14:12,960 --> 00:14:14,170
I think so.

337
00:14:15,030 --> 00:14:15,870
Fast.

338
00:14:15,870 --> 00:14:16,770
Go get me a ticket back
to the main island. Hurry.

339
00:14:16,770 --> 00:14:17,300
Hurry up.

340
00:14:17,300 --> 00:14:18,200
Why are you going back to the main island?

341
00:14:18,200 --> 00:14:19,570
Go buy it first.

342
00:14:19,570 --> 00:14:20,840
If you don't tell me why,
I'm not buying it.

343
00:14:20,840 --> 00:14:22,370
My house is about to be sold!

344
00:14:28,240 --> 00:14:30,170
So that's how your debt came about.

345
00:14:31,150 --> 00:14:32,610
It's really infuriating.

346
00:14:33,150 --> 00:14:34,390
Back then, when I called your boss,

347
00:14:34,390 --> 00:14:36,250
I should've chewed him out.

348
00:14:42,790 --> 00:14:44,670
How did it turn out like this?

349
00:14:47,370 --> 00:14:49,430
It's all because
of that stupid shooting star.

350
00:14:49,430 --> 00:14:51,370
I'm completely stuck now.

351
00:14:54,640 --> 00:14:56,710
You can't blame the shooting star, either.

352
00:14:56,710 --> 00:14:58,640
Anyway, it has already happened.

353
00:14:59,550 --> 00:15:00,240
Right.

354
00:15:01,110 --> 00:15:03,310
Since it has happened, I have to face it.

355
00:15:03,550 --> 00:15:04,720
I'll pay my own debt myself.

356
00:15:04,720 --> 00:15:06,120
No one can touch my house.

357
00:15:06,530 --> 00:15:08,170
Are you going to help me
buy the ticket or not?

358
00:15:08,170 --> 00:15:09,450
What can buying a ticket do?

359
00:15:09,450 --> 00:15:11,020
Can you do anything
if you go back to the main island?

360
00:15:11,020 --> 00:15:12,290
I don't care.

361
00:15:12,930 --> 00:15:14,120
My dad is selling the house for me now.

362
00:15:14,120 --> 00:15:16,120
I can't just sit here and do nothing.

363
00:15:16,820 --> 00:15:18,750
I'm going back to confront my boss.

364
00:15:20,850 --> 00:15:22,250
Fine, you want to go back.

365
00:15:22,260 --> 00:15:24,060
Do you have money? Do you have an ID?

366
00:15:24,060 --> 00:15:26,320
That's why I'm asking you
to buy it for me.

367
00:15:26,640 --> 00:15:28,200
Fine, if I buy it for you, and then?

368
00:15:28,200 --> 00:15:30,170
How are you going to come up
with that five million?

369
00:15:30,170 --> 00:15:31,440
Even if you go to a loan shark now,

370
00:15:31,440 --> 00:15:32,210
no one's gonna lend you anything,

371
00:15:32,210 --> 00:15:33,040
you know?

372
00:15:33,240 --> 00:15:35,700
And in what capacity
will you face your boss?

373
00:15:54,220 --> 00:15:55,320
Mr. He,

374
00:15:56,980 --> 00:15:58,510
since you are so reluctant,

375
00:15:59,580 --> 00:16:00,960
why must you sell it?

376
00:16:07,540 --> 00:16:08,710
Well,

377
00:16:10,530 --> 00:16:14,260
there are always times when one is forced
to act against their will.

378
00:16:43,250 --> 00:16:44,310
I'm sorry.

379
00:16:49,950 --> 00:16:50,990
Haowei.

380
00:16:51,850 --> 00:16:54,120
Go take an inventory
of that driftwood for me.

381
00:16:54,120 --> 00:16:54,930
Okay.

382
00:18:32,560 --> 00:18:34,530
Village Chief, we can handle it here.

383
00:18:34,530 --> 00:18:35,890
I already finished this downstairs.

384
00:18:35,890 --> 00:18:36,630
Okay.

385
00:18:36,930 --> 00:18:37,490
How is it?

386
00:18:37,490 --> 00:18:38,530
How is the fire going?

387
00:18:38,530 --> 00:18:39,860
It's fine. It's okay.

388
00:18:40,110 --> 00:18:41,710
You're fanning very slowly.

389
00:18:41,730 --> 00:18:42,770
Let me do it.

390
00:18:43,100 --> 00:18:44,030
Yue, help me check that ice.

391
00:18:44,030 --> 00:18:45,340
-Being a village chief is really hard work.
-You do it.

392
00:18:45,340 --> 00:18:46,270
You've gotta do everything yourself.

393
00:18:46,270 --> 00:18:47,100
I'm afraid there won't be enough alcohol.

394
00:18:47,100 --> 00:18:49,360
If you're not the Village Chief later...

395
00:18:49,870 --> 00:18:52,010
♪ Happy birthday to you ♪

396
00:18:52,010 --> 00:18:55,210
♪ Happy birthday to you ♪

397
00:18:55,370 --> 00:18:58,120
♪ Happy birthday to you ♪

398
00:18:58,150 --> 00:19:00,020
Thank you.

399
00:19:00,020 --> 00:19:01,120
Wait.

400
00:19:01,410 --> 00:19:02,420
You have to make a wish first.

401
00:19:02,420 --> 00:19:03,790
It's our Xingpu Island tradition.

402
00:19:03,790 --> 00:19:04,520
Make a wish.

403
00:19:04,520 --> 00:19:05,320
Make a wish.

404
00:19:07,260 --> 00:19:08,320
Okay, here it goes.

405
00:19:10,100 --> 00:19:10,690
OK.

406
00:19:12,330 --> 00:19:13,390
Alright, alright.

407
00:19:15,170 --> 00:19:16,730
Cheers.

408
00:19:16,970 --> 00:19:17,630
Come, let's have a drink.

409
00:19:17,630 --> 00:19:19,340
To the most handsome Hua of Xingpu Island.

410
00:19:19,340 --> 00:19:20,200
Good.

411
00:19:20,640 --> 00:19:21,970
I wish everyone good health.

412
00:19:21,970 --> 00:19:23,830
And may all your wishes come true.

413
00:19:27,740 --> 00:19:29,610
You young people, get moving.

414
00:19:30,100 --> 00:19:31,630
Tell me what you want to eat.

415
00:19:34,820 --> 00:19:35,820
What do you want to eat?

416
00:19:35,820 --> 00:19:36,390
Green peppers.

417
00:19:36,390 --> 00:19:36,780
Okay.

418
00:19:36,990 --> 00:19:37,790
And what else?

419
00:19:40,020 --> 00:19:40,620
Mushrooms.

420
00:19:40,620 --> 00:19:41,060
Mushrooms?

421
00:19:41,060 --> 00:19:41,660
Right.

422
00:19:44,160 --> 00:19:45,460
Come to think of it,

423
00:19:46,130 --> 00:19:49,070
it seems you've been on Xingpu Island
for 16 years already.

424
00:19:49,070 --> 00:19:49,630
Yeah.

425
00:19:49,630 --> 00:19:50,630
Yeah, about that.

426
00:19:51,500 --> 00:19:52,140
Even

427
00:19:52,140 --> 00:19:55,000
Yang Guo would've reunited
with Xiaolongnü by now.

428
00:19:55,800 --> 00:19:57,460
That's such an old reference.

429
00:19:57,660 --> 00:20:00,920
Have you never thought
about going back to the main island?

430
00:20:03,510 --> 00:20:04,910
I brought this on myself.

431
00:20:05,280 --> 00:20:06,680
Better if I don't go back.

432
00:20:06,930 --> 00:20:07,480
Right.

433
00:20:08,220 --> 00:20:09,090
You are guilty.

434
00:20:10,050 --> 00:20:10,990
Your sin, well,

435
00:20:10,990 --> 00:20:12,390
is that you aren't drunk enough.

436
00:20:12,390 --> 00:20:13,030
Exactly.

437
00:20:13,320 --> 00:20:14,630
Before you get drunk,

438
00:20:14,630 --> 00:20:15,770
you're not going anywhere.

439
00:20:15,770 --> 00:20:16,660
Do you all remember?

440
00:20:16,660 --> 00:20:18,460
Every time he buys a boat ticket,

441
00:20:18,560 --> 00:20:21,570
something always goes wrong.

442
00:20:21,590 --> 00:20:23,790
You and the main island

443
00:20:23,900 --> 00:20:25,970
just don't mix.

444
00:20:27,200 --> 00:20:27,970
Bottoms up.

445
00:20:31,540 --> 00:20:32,280
What's up?

446
00:20:32,280 --> 00:20:33,540
I can't drink anymore.

447
00:20:34,610 --> 00:20:36,380
I was just kidding.

448
00:20:36,430 --> 00:20:38,360
There are still ingredients here.

449
00:20:42,420 --> 00:20:44,250
Xiaoyou, eat with us.

450
00:20:45,360 --> 00:20:46,290
No, thanks.

451
00:20:46,590 --> 00:20:48,390
I don't have much of an appetite.

452
00:20:48,550 --> 00:20:50,210
Then, let's have a drink.

453
00:20:51,040 --> 00:20:52,770
Come on, let's drink together.

454
00:20:53,490 --> 00:20:54,630
I'll help myself.

455
00:20:54,660 --> 00:20:56,630
Drink some more.

456
00:20:59,500 --> 00:21:00,230
Uncle Hua.

457
00:21:01,210 --> 00:21:02,210
Happy birthday to you.

458
00:21:02,210 --> 00:21:02,970
Thank you.

459
00:21:03,400 --> 00:21:05,740
And I wish you all the best
and that everything goes smoothly.

460
00:21:05,740 --> 00:21:06,940
Thank you, Uncle Hua.

461
00:21:10,810 --> 00:21:11,950
What's wrong? Are you not feeling well?

462
00:21:11,950 --> 00:21:12,820
Let me take a look.

463
00:21:12,820 --> 00:21:14,420
No need, I'll be fine
after I go back and sleep for a bit.

464
00:21:14,420 --> 00:21:15,990
Have him take a look at you here，
no charge.

465
00:21:15,990 --> 00:21:16,620
Right.

466
00:21:16,620 --> 00:21:18,590
Your problem is
that you haven't had enough to drink.

467
00:21:18,590 --> 00:21:19,660
Toast the Village Chief.

468
00:21:19,660 --> 00:21:20,560
Let me have a drink with you.

469
00:21:20,560 --> 00:21:21,200
Come.

470
00:21:24,600 --> 00:21:25,530
Drink some more.

471
00:21:25,720 --> 00:21:26,400
Right.

472
00:21:29,720 --> 00:21:30,380
Uncle Hua.

473
00:21:31,100 --> 00:21:31,600
Yesterday...

474
00:21:31,600 --> 00:21:32,470
It's nothing.

475
00:21:32,470 --> 00:21:34,260
Let's talk about yesterday's matter later.

476
00:21:34,260 --> 00:21:35,060
It's nothing.

477
00:21:36,640 --> 00:21:38,280
Come, let's drink together.

478
00:21:38,540 --> 00:21:40,670
Aren't you going to drink with Angela?

479
00:21:42,300 --> 00:21:43,300
To Angela.

480
00:21:44,360 --> 00:21:45,370
You drink half.

481
00:21:50,120 --> 00:21:50,920
That's enough, Li Wanzhe.

482
00:21:50,920 --> 00:21:52,300
Stop drinking.

483
00:21:55,860 --> 00:21:57,130
-Village Chief Wang.
-Watch me perform.

484
00:21:57,130 --> 00:21:59,990
Thank you, Village Chief Wang,
for your usual care.

485
00:22:00,100 --> 00:22:00,700
Come.

486
00:22:00,930 --> 00:22:02,430
Village Chief Wang, let's drink.

487
00:22:02,430 --> 00:22:03,470
You're very thirsty, aren't you?

488
00:22:03,470 --> 00:22:04,600
Wait a moment, I need to go pee first.

489
00:22:04,600 --> 00:22:05,140
I'm going to pee first.

490
00:22:05,140 --> 00:22:05,670
Village Chief Wang.

491
00:22:05,670 --> 00:22:06,540
You drink first.

492
00:22:06,540 --> 00:22:08,170
Where are you going, Village Chief Wang?

493
00:22:08,170 --> 00:22:09,840
Are you running away?
Doing your usual bathroom escape?

494
00:22:09,840 --> 00:22:10,910
He's like this every time.

495
00:22:10,910 --> 00:22:11,830
I'm done grilling over there.

496
00:22:11,830 --> 00:22:13,760
I'll come and drink with everyone.

497
00:22:19,240 --> 00:22:20,510
I'll drink with you.

498
00:22:23,190 --> 00:22:24,200
Li Wanzhe.

499
00:22:26,020 --> 00:22:27,080
Where's Li Wanzhe?

500
00:22:27,390 --> 00:22:29,190
Li Wanzhe is dancing over there.

501
00:22:34,830 --> 00:22:36,490
Carp Leaping the Dragon Gate!

502
00:22:37,080 --> 00:22:37,550
Come.

503
00:22:46,610 --> 00:22:48,850
Having a son like Li Wanzhe, I seriously
don't know what to do with him.

504
00:22:48,850 --> 00:22:49,750
Is he really my son?

505
00:22:49,750 --> 00:22:50,780
Of course, he is your son.

506
00:22:50,780 --> 00:22:51,520
-He's good enough already.
-I don't know.

507
00:22:51,520 --> 00:22:52,480
Sometimes I'm not sure.

508
00:22:52,480 --> 00:22:53,380
I'm not sure.

509
00:22:53,880 --> 00:22:55,050
You can be unsure?

510
00:22:55,750 --> 00:22:56,880
I'll drink with you.

511
00:23:10,420 --> 00:23:11,460
I'm sorry.

512
00:23:14,540 --> 00:23:15,940
It's all my fault.

513
00:23:18,040 --> 00:23:18,510
Hua.

514
00:23:18,510 --> 00:23:20,080
Will you forgive me?

515
00:23:20,110 --> 00:23:21,450
He's had these symptoms for a long time.

516
00:23:21,450 --> 00:23:22,710
Do you have any medicine to give him?

517
00:23:22,710 --> 00:23:23,280
Help him.

518
00:23:23,280 --> 00:23:24,080
Don't ignore me.

519
00:23:24,080 --> 00:23:24,950
I have medicine.

520
00:23:24,950 --> 00:23:26,920
Give him a few more drinks,

521
00:23:26,920 --> 00:23:28,050
then he'll be quiet.

522
00:23:28,050 --> 00:23:29,550
Drink more.

523
00:23:29,550 --> 00:23:31,220
Come, drink.

524
00:23:32,860 --> 00:23:34,590
He's still mixing people up.

525
00:23:35,090 --> 00:23:36,060
Dad.

526
00:23:36,060 --> 00:23:36,930
Mr. He, I'm sorry.

527
00:23:36,930 --> 00:23:38,230
Xiaoyou, you're drunk.

528
00:23:38,230 --> 00:23:38,600
Xiaoyou.

529
00:23:38,600 --> 00:23:39,750
Don't touch me.

530
00:23:40,000 --> 00:23:41,130
Luckily, our Li Wanzhe

531
00:23:41,130 --> 00:23:42,630
doesn't just recognize anyone as his dad.

532
00:23:42,630 --> 00:23:43,770
You won't drink with me?

533
00:23:43,770 --> 00:23:44,470
Go to sleep.

534
00:23:44,470 --> 00:23:45,930
I'm not drinking with you.

535
00:23:49,880 --> 00:23:51,680
You want to drink with me, right?

536
00:23:52,120 --> 00:23:53,580
Fine, I'll drink with you.

537
00:24:00,100 --> 00:24:00,630
Xiaoyou.

538
00:24:01,210 --> 00:24:01,880
Let's go.

539
00:24:02,350 --> 00:24:03,150
Xiaoyou.

540
00:24:03,970 --> 00:24:05,900
That wine is quite expensive.

541
00:24:06,630 --> 00:24:07,630
I'll take care of him.

542
00:24:07,630 --> 00:24:08,550
-Take some more.
-Xiaoyou.

543
00:24:08,550 --> 00:24:09,410
Take some more.

544
00:24:13,870 --> 00:24:14,800
Xiaoyou.

545
00:24:14,930 --> 00:24:16,130
Is something wrong with his head?

546
00:24:16,130 --> 00:24:17,660
Xiaoyou, walk a bit slower.

547
00:24:26,800 --> 00:24:28,530
Where exactly do you want to go?

548
00:24:42,370 --> 00:24:43,790
That's enough, don't drink anymore.

549
00:24:43,790 --> 00:24:44,460
You've had too much.

550
00:24:44,460 --> 00:24:45,530
Don't touch me!

551
00:24:49,970 --> 00:24:52,700
If you don't want to drink,
you just go back first.

552
00:24:52,900 --> 00:24:54,600
Don't mind me, okay?

553
00:24:56,970 --> 00:24:58,070
Alright.

554
00:24:58,780 --> 00:25:00,580
Let's go back to the guesthouse.

555
00:25:00,940 --> 00:25:02,180
What guesthouse?

556
00:25:04,280 --> 00:25:05,780
I'm telling you,

557
00:25:06,860 --> 00:25:08,660
if I don't finish the wine today,

558
00:25:09,150 --> 00:25:10,820
I'm not going back.

559
00:25:11,500 --> 00:25:12,560
Do you understand?

560
00:25:16,860 --> 00:25:17,910
You're drunk.

561
00:25:19,430 --> 00:25:20,490
What are you doing?

562
00:25:23,570 --> 00:25:24,510
I'm telling you,

563
00:25:26,300 --> 00:25:28,100
if I don't finish the wine today,

564
00:25:28,410 --> 00:25:29,910
I'm not going back.

565
00:25:31,070 --> 00:25:31,980
What are you doing?

566
00:25:31,980 --> 00:25:32,940
Stop drinking.

567
00:25:34,410 --> 00:25:35,050
Xiaoyou.

568
00:25:35,480 --> 00:25:36,750
Alright, alright.

569
00:25:36,750 --> 00:25:38,480
Don't grab my wine!

570
00:25:38,790 --> 00:25:40,230
You've drunk too much.

571
00:25:48,380 --> 00:25:49,280
Okay, well...

572
00:25:53,460 --> 00:25:54,860
I'll finish this bottle,

573
00:25:54,900 --> 00:25:57,500
and then we'll go back
to the guesthouse, okay?

574
00:25:59,090 --> 00:26:00,270
You said it.

575
00:26:15,240 --> 00:26:16,660
Is there something wrong with his head?

576
00:26:16,660 --> 00:26:18,320
He's possessed or something.

577
00:26:19,740 --> 00:26:21,040
Grab your wine, hurry up.

578
00:26:21,040 --> 00:26:22,900
Let's go over and toast Uncle Hua.

579
00:26:22,930 --> 00:26:23,530
Hurry up!

580
00:26:23,530 --> 00:26:24,430
This must be hereditary.

581
00:26:24,430 --> 00:26:25,180
Hurry up.

582
00:26:25,210 --> 00:26:26,130
Hereditary? From whom?

583
00:26:26,130 --> 00:26:28,470
From a medical point
of view, it's genetic.

584
00:26:28,470 --> 00:26:29,380
Uncle Hua.

585
00:26:29,730 --> 00:26:30,700
Happy birthday to you.

586
00:26:30,700 --> 00:26:31,070
Thank you, everyone.

587
00:26:31,070 --> 00:26:32,170
Happy birthday.

588
00:26:32,460 --> 00:26:33,350
And Mr. He.

589
00:26:34,250 --> 00:26:35,170
Thank you.

590
00:26:35,840 --> 00:26:37,310
Thank you, Home at He's.

591
00:26:37,670 --> 00:26:39,310
I really like it here.

592
00:26:39,340 --> 00:26:42,810
Cheers!

593
00:26:42,840 --> 00:26:44,990
I really can't bear to see it sold.

594
00:26:45,020 --> 00:26:46,220
Okay, you've had too much.

595
00:26:46,220 --> 00:26:47,820
Let's go over there
and watch the dancing, okay?

596
00:26:47,820 --> 00:26:48,790
Let's go, let's go dancing.

597
00:26:48,790 --> 00:26:49,890
Let's go, let's go dancing together.

598
00:26:49,890 --> 00:26:50,750
Let's go.

599
00:26:50,750 --> 00:26:52,220
Let's go, let's go dancing.

600
00:26:52,220 --> 00:26:53,520
Let's go dancing.

601
00:26:53,990 --> 00:26:55,690
I like it here very much.

602
00:26:55,820 --> 00:26:57,620
It's the girls' turn to dance.

603
00:26:58,160 --> 00:26:59,560
The girls' turn to dance.

604
00:27:00,750 --> 00:27:02,080
What did he mean by that?

605
00:27:05,380 --> 00:27:06,650
I sold the guesthouse.

606
00:27:08,020 --> 00:27:09,020
You sold it?

607
00:27:10,560 --> 00:27:11,980
Well, come.

608
00:27:12,310 --> 00:27:13,370
Today is my birthday.

609
00:27:13,370 --> 00:27:14,320
Don't talk about this.

610
00:27:14,320 --> 00:27:16,180
That's not the point today, okay?

611
00:27:16,650 --> 00:27:17,250
But he...

612
00:27:17,250 --> 00:27:18,050
It is.

613
00:27:18,050 --> 00:27:18,910
What about him?

614
00:27:18,950 --> 00:27:21,050
-Aye...
-A, B, C, D, okay?

615
00:27:21,050 --> 00:27:22,550
You're so annoying.

616
00:27:30,730 --> 00:27:32,130
The alcohol is finished.

617
00:27:32,260 --> 00:27:34,090
Let's go home.

618
00:27:40,750 --> 00:27:42,280
You're going the wrong way.

619
00:27:58,520 --> 00:27:59,920
Can you tell me now?

620
00:28:00,960 --> 00:28:02,690
What exactly are you sad about?

621
00:28:04,060 --> 00:28:05,380
Am I sad?

622
00:28:06,630 --> 00:28:08,970
I'm super happy.

623
00:28:09,730 --> 00:28:12,970
I drank the most alcohol in my life today.

624
00:28:12,970 --> 00:28:14,370
Tell me the truth.

625
00:28:15,540 --> 00:28:18,210
I'm happy. I'm great.

626
00:28:18,210 --> 00:28:20,480
Don't grab me.

627
00:28:21,030 --> 00:28:22,940
I can walk by myself.

628
00:28:29,150 --> 00:28:30,050
Chen Haowei.

629
00:28:30,180 --> 00:28:31,660
Don't come looking for me ever again.

630
00:28:31,660 --> 00:28:32,590
What do you mean?

631
00:28:32,770 --> 00:28:34,570
He Xiangyong.

632
00:28:41,920 --> 00:28:44,380
You just turn around
and walk away like that.

633
00:28:47,200 --> 00:28:49,930
You just turned around
and walked away like that.

634
00:28:53,200 --> 00:28:55,000
It wasn't easy for me to find you.

635
00:28:56,410 --> 00:28:58,210
I'm not letting you go this time.

636
00:29:00,050 --> 00:29:01,010
He Xiangyong.

637
00:29:38,740 --> 00:29:40,610
Page eighteen isn't on the exam.

638
00:29:39,090 --> 00:29:44,610
[Epilogue]

639
00:29:40,690 --> 00:29:43,290
Happy birthday to you.

640
00:29:45,860 --> 00:29:48,160
This is the first time
I've drawn a picture for someone.

641
00:29:48,160 --> 00:29:49,600
I hope you don't dislike it.

642
00:29:49,600 --> 00:29:50,800
Dislike it?

643
00:29:51,800 --> 00:29:53,830
This is the best birthday gift
I've ever received.

644
00:29:53,830 --> 00:29:55,630
How could I possibly dislike it?

645
00:29:56,240 --> 00:29:58,530
I like it very, very, very much.

646
00:30:00,040 --> 00:30:01,010
That's good.

647
00:30:06,490 --> 00:30:07,980
How could you forget
the most important part?

648
00:30:07,980 --> 00:30:09,980
The signature—hurry up and sign it.

649
00:30:10,720 --> 00:30:11,760
When you become famous in the future,

650
00:30:11,760 --> 00:30:12,420
I'll show off to everyone

651
00:30:12,420 --> 00:30:13,820
that I was your first fan.

652
00:30:14,150 --> 00:30:15,880
You're so dramatic.

653
00:30:16,510 --> 00:30:17,450
He Xiangyong.

654
00:30:18,330 --> 00:30:19,000
One day,

655
00:30:19,000 --> 00:30:22,000
you will surely become
a world-famous great painter.

656
00:30:23,170 --> 00:30:25,570
You're so hyped
for this year's birthday gift.

657
00:30:25,570 --> 00:30:27,230
What am I going to do next year?

658
00:30:27,840 --> 00:30:30,370
How about on my birthday next year,

659
00:30:30,370 --> 00:30:31,540
you take me back to your home

660
00:30:31,540 --> 00:30:32,640
to see real sea turtles?

661
00:30:32,640 --> 00:30:34,040
Okay, it's a deal.

662
00:30:35,870 --> 00:30:37,140
At that time, we

663
00:30:37,880 --> 00:30:39,150
didn't know

664
00:30:39,980 --> 00:30:41,080
these words...

665
00:30:41,920 --> 00:30:43,720
had no chance to come true later.

666
00:31:09,130 --> 00:31:15,900
[Next Episode]

667
00:31:09,480 --> 00:31:10,180
So last night,

668
00:31:10,180 --> 00:31:11,710
you and Chen Haowei kissed.

669
00:31:12,220 --> 00:31:13,620
So happy.

670
00:31:13,620 --> 00:31:15,750
You said it while holding me like this.

671
00:31:16,020 --> 00:31:17,820
The wish has come true like this.

672
00:31:17,850 --> 00:31:20,920
Don't you feel it's a bit unsettling?

673
00:31:21,480 --> 00:31:23,300
What I'm thinking of in my heart
is He Xiangyong.

674
00:31:23,300 --> 00:31:25,200
I shouldn't use Xiaoyou as his substitute.

